Also the fact that 2 national parks have been authorized by the government will be of great economic importance, with more money being invested and more money being made due to more people visiting the country and at the same time spending money. Since Slovenia is a small country, it is entered from three sides by Italy, Austria and Hungary, but Slovenia does not have access to the sea. It is located in the centre of South Eastern Europe. Although the three neighbours are so close, Slovenia is the most underdeveloped country from the EU neighbouring countries. Not as developed as Italy, and Hungary and Austria are as far as economy is considered, to go deeper into it.

Because of its cooperation with such industrial powerhouses as Germany, they are the roots and foundation of the economy on which it relies, and is focused. Nowadays, because of the lowered importance of coal mining and steel production, metalworking is the main activity in Slovenia, along with tourism, which is on the increase.

Tourism on the increase

Slovenia tourism industry is improving and earning the country more money year after year. There are many improvements having been or being made to roads, railways and supplying safe drinking water. Also for the London population, Barcelona, Madrid and Prague welcomes millions of tourists and visitors each year respectively, employing hundreds of thousands of workers, especially the more popular tourist spots.
